move_plan.prompt:
Public environment information: {environment->public_information}
Your private information: {agents->agent_1->private_information}
Global goal: {agents->agent_1->goal}
Provide a step-by-step ordered list of primitive moves you will perform to contribute toward the global goal. Each move must be legal under Tower of Hanoi rules and must move only disks A, B, C, or D. If you cannot determine some moves because they depend on other agents, provide the moves you can perform unambiguously.

Public environment information: {environment->public_information}
Your private information: {agents->agent_2->private_information}
Global goal: {agents->agent_2->goal}
Provide a step-by-step ordered list of primitive moves you will perform to contribute toward the global goal. Each move must be legal under Tower of Hanoi rules and must move only disks E, F, or G. If you cannot determine some moves because they depend on other agents, provide the moves you can perform unambiguously.

Public environment information: {environment->public_information}
Your private information: {agents->agent_3->private_information}
Global goal: {agents->agent_3->goal}
Provide a step-by-step ordered list of primitive moves you will perform to contribute toward the global goal. Each move must be legal under Tower of Hanoi rules and must move only disks H, I, or J. If you cannot determine some moves because they depend on other agents, provide the moves you can perform unambiguously.

pddl.prompt:
You will receive ordered primitive move lists from the three agents. Your task: 1) validate and, if needed, reorder or complement their moves to produce a single legal sequence that reaches the goal, making no assumptions beyond the public information and agents' private permissions; 2) produce a PDDL domain and problem suitable for FastDownwards capturing the multi-agent actions and the concrete instance. Here are the agents' move lists:
{moves_agent_1}
{moves_agent_2}
{moves_agent_3}
Integrate them, keep agent action names distinct, and emit the PDDL domain and problem as required. If the agents' move lists are partial, fill in only what is logically necessary to reach the goal without violating agent permissions.
